.SH NAME
scsi_remove_single_device \- Respond to user request to remove a device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" scsi_remove_single_device
.BI "(uint host "  ","
.BI "uint channel "  ","
.BI "uint id "  ","
.BI "uint lun "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "host" 12
user-supplied decimal integer
.IP "channel" 12
user-supplied decimal integer
.IP "id" 12
user-supplied decimal integer
.IP "lun" 12
user-supplied decimal integer
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
called by writing "scsi remove-single-device" to
/proc/scsi/scsi.  Does a \fBscsi_device_lookup\fP and \fBscsi_remove_device\fP
